            <h3>Learn about refugees</h3>
            <hr style=" border-color:black;" />
            <p>
                Have you ever wondered about who is a refugee? Or are you confused with the difference between a refugee and an asylum seeker?<br />
                <br />
                Refugees are generally referred to people who have been forced to flee from their homes due to many reasons including violence, conflict, and war. A refugee fears returning to their home country because of the ill-treatment or violence that they may face for reasons of race, religion, nationality, political opinion.<br />
                <br/>
                Asylum Seekers are people who are seeking international protection for their fear of persecution in their home country. They are claiming to be in a refugee-like situation and are seeking legal protection, however, their claim for refugee status has not yet been officially determined.<br />
                <br/>
                You can read the definition of refugees and asylum seekers as per United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) <a target="_blank" href="https://www.unrefugees.org/refugee-facts/what-is-a-refugee/">here</a>.
            </p>

